24/01/2007
ANKARA, Turkey -- Parliament held a closed-door session Tuesday (January 23rd) regarding the situation in Iraq, classifying comments to prevent future leaks. Ankara recently has indicated growing concerns over the alleged continued presence of the terrorist organisation Kurdistan Workers Party in northern Iraq, as well as the situation in Kirkuk.
In other news, former Turkish Foreign Minister Ismail Cem, 67, died on Wednesday of lung cancer. He served as Turkey's top diplomat in three successive governments between 1997 and 2002 and is credited with strengthening relations with neighbouring Greece. (Milliyet, Cihan - 24/01/07; Zaman - 23/01/07)
